*Work in progress*

0. compile:
	requirements: libpcap, pthreads
	to build it type: gcc -O2 -lpcap -lpthread -o ra ra.c
	to run it: ./ra -i interface -p prefix -l prefix_len (default 64)
0.1 tested on:
	freebsd 8,macos x 10-7,linux fedora 13

1. usage:

usage: ra -i ifname(em0) -l prefix_len(64) -p prefix -m mtu(1500) -f flags (read below) -r times(read below) -l advertise_interval(default 30 seconds)

so if you run
	ra -p dead:beef:dead:beef::
will run:
	ra -i em0 -m 1500 -l 64 -p dead:beef:dead:beef:: -f 'ra_managed' -t 30 -r 4294967295:4294967295:60:60:60

see RFC 4862 for more info
available flags: pi_onlink pi_autonomous ra_managed ra_ha ra_other ra_pref_(high|low)
	flags must be in 1 argument eg.: -f "ra_managed ra_pref_medium pi_onlink"
available times: pi_valid_time:pi_preferred_time:ra_lifetime:ra_reachable:ra_retransmit
	 must be in 1 argument, and all defined eg.: -r 4294967295:4294967295:60:60:60
		pi_valid_time:4294967295 - infinity, specify prefix valid time
		pi_preferred_time:4294967295 - infinity, specify prefix preferred time

